{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sidekiq/sidekiq/issues/5806","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sidekiq/sidekiq","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sidekiq/sidekiq/issues/5806/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sidekiq/sidekiq/issues/5806/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sidekiq/sidekiq/issues/5806/events","html_url":"https://github.com/sidekiq/sidekiq/issues/5806","id":1599257607,"node_id":"I_kwDOADDA9M5fUrwH","number":5806,"title":"Return values for sidekiq_retry_in must now be integers not ","user":{"login":"RobsonKing","id":7375349,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjczNzUzNDk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7375349?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/RobsonKing","html_url":"https://github.com/RobsonKing","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RobsonKing/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RobsonKing/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RobsonKing/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RobsonKing/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RobsonKing/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RobsonKing/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RobsonKing/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RobsonKing/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/RobsonKing/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2023-02-24T20:46:38Z","updated_at":"2023-02-24T21:35:56Z","closed_at":"2023-02-24T21:34:51Z","author_association":"NONE","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"During our upgrade from sidekiq 5.2.9 (pro 5.0.0) to sidekiq 6.5.8 (pro 5.5.8)\r\n\r\nWe encountered a problem where our jobs using sidekiq_retry_in were no longer respecting their custom interval. \r\n\r\nExample job\r\n```\r\n  class RetryDelay < ApplicationSidekiqWorker\r\n\r\n    sidekiq_retry_in { 1.day }\r\n    def perform\r\n      raise \"boom\"\r\n    end\r\n  end\r\n```\r\n\r\nafter digging around I believe that the change:\r\nhttps://github.com/sidekiq/sidekiq/pull/5432/files\r\n\r\nresulted in only integers being accepted as valid return values from sidekiq_retry_in.  We fixed our code by changing\r\n\r\n`sidekiq_retry_in { 1.day }`\r\n to \r\n`sidekiq_retry_in { 1.day.to_i }`\r\n\r\nIf this change was intentional, may I suggest logging a message to the console if a non integer is returned from sidekiq_retry_in?  This might save someone else a bunch of time debugging.\r\n\r\nThanks for the great work!\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"mperham","id":2911,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5MTE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2911?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mperham","html_url":"https://github.com/mperham","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mperham/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mperham/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mperham/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mperham/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mperham/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mperham/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mperham/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mperham/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mperham/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sidekiq/sidekiq/issues/5806/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":